public class ClassMetadataConverter<T>
extends ConverterDecorator<T>

Converter responsible of writing and reading @class metadata. This is useful if you want to be able to deserialize all serialized objects without knowing their real type. Metadata is written only in objects (never in arrays or literals) and is always the first element in the object. Most default converters are annotated with @HandleClassMetada indicating that they will not have class metadata written nor use it during deserialization.

Author:
eugen
